In Need for Speed: The Run it competes all over America.
Reviewed
A trip, in principle carefree, gets complicated because of a series of improper carelessness of a routine trip during the morning shift.
To some extent the expectations were met, but this is of no use, if, in fact, nothing extraordinary was intended to be done.
The new installment, to which The Run is added to the title, aroused high expectations already before its premiere.
It promised that it would give new airs to the old Need for Speed racing saga and, as a result of what is shown, it appears as a game that should not end up again being an action genre without more.
We are also curious to know what the inserted scenes would look like, where the main character descends from the car and walks on his own foot.
As is often the case in the NFS series, the results do not differ much from what we expected.
There are races that can be considered acceptable, but in total count points are lost due to absurd failures, which have already appeared in the series for years.
In reality, they cannot even be called errors, but rather it is the incomprehensible mischief of programmers.
The adventure starts very well.
It introduces you to a story, whose protagonist, Jack, has certain personal problems; to solve them, he is offered to participate in an illegal race throughout America.
You sit behind the wheel on the west coast, in San Francisco, and your mission is to get first to New York.
The idea is to offer something interesting.
The route is divided into ten stages and then more than fifty races.
It follows that each race takes place on a different route and the stages are located in different environments, which are quite different and interesting.
In this way, one does not even remotely have the feeling that the game always offers the same thing.
Some of the environments are even pleasing to the eye, although the technical level of the graph is equivalent to that of previous deliveries of the series.
Therefore, it is nothing of the other world.
But the walk through the desert, the autumn landscape or the high snow-covered mountains produce a very pleasant visual effect.
In addition, races are diversified from time to time by an atypical element.
So, for example, in the desert you find a sandstorm that decreases visibility.
But in the mountains, be careful not to be buried by an avalanche.
According to that, each of the races is very well developed.
There are only a couple of models, but that's enough.
For a moment, you try to overtake a required number of opponents (normal in a classic race), then you try to gain time (timed classic duel) and then a duel against a single opponent awaits you.
In the midst of all this, the police sometimes appear, which only make things even more difficult.
The novelty is the landscapes outside the car.
Interactive animations are presented when Jack, in most cases, has to escape from someone and you have to help him, always pressing the button just at the right time.
Nothing complicated.
It is surprising, however, that there are far fewer landscapes in the game than would be expected (in particular there are only three).
But the end result is positive, because this element does not become annoying and, in the aforementioned context, is one of the elements that make the game more interesting.
The driving model follows in the footsteps of the previous episodes.
This means that today it is no longer a big deal, but it cannot be said to be bad.
If you are looking for a realistic simulation, you can search elsewhere.
But a race designed with plenty of action is quite suitable for this driving style, although we can find something better among the games of the competition.
So far, everything in order.
But problems arise after a certain time.
Unlike the correct driving models, the same is no longer the case with collisions.
From games of this type it is not expected to recreate complicated deformations and collisions, but in fact before a blow against any object, you cannot predict how your car will react, with which not everything is in order.
It is typical that, when making a very tight overtaking or driving the car with normal traffic, there are only slight frictions, but in other almost identical situations, your car ends up making uncontrolled pirouettes.
Or it even ends up totally destroyed.
Thanks to the reset system, no big problems arise, but it can put you in a bad mood.
The resets are programmed in such a way that, when you suffer an accident or leave the track, the game restores you to the last rescue point on the track.
However, in each race only five resets are available.
If you consume them all, you have to restart the race from the beginning.
So it is only a help in case something goes wrong, but it is not very trustworthy.
Sometimes, not even the reset helps, it only helps to learn the given stage from memory.
A major disadvantage of the game is that the same facts are repeated in different places.
In some curves, for example, you have to enter in a specific way; otherwise, they are impossible to take.
Other times you will find yourself somewhere "civil vehicles" always with the same configuration, even if you are the first, fifth or arrive five minutes before or after.
This makes you angry especially in situations, when you see two cars that go to meet in opposite directions, your opponent advances without problems, but when you arrive, you must turn or brake.
It is the same when you arrive, because it is programmed so that the “surprise” will always happen before your nose.
The opponents also have one more advantage.
Throughout the game you will get to places where, regardless of the moment, the same opponent will always lead you in the same place.
In addition, this happens at the end of the game, on a long bridge, which is even more shocking.
Your opponent must come before you, at whatever price.
When it goes in front of you, it makes it difficult for you to see the cars coming in front of you, so at first you can make the car porridge.
You can understand the idea of creating a game with maximum doses of suspense and adrenaline, but the execution is so apparent that it will surely disappoint you right away.
And it’s a shame, because even though the model of the trip is simple, the game is fun and action-packed, so it’s often not possible to follow in detail what happens or where.
And it really doesn’t matter, whether the merit takes the idea with fifty exclusive tracks or qualifying in the race so it doesn’t fit the boredom, or anything else.
An unusual idea is changing cars during races.
You have to be attentive to the gasoline suppliers next to the road, because precisely there you have to change cars, although in the vast majority of cases you will be enough what you have.
Cars are divided into three categories.
Sports cars are suitable for urban areas, American strong cars for straight highways and exotic supercars for technical driving, for example, on curved mountain roads.
In addition to main narrative thread also appears a thread of parallel challenges, that is, there are races in specific places that you will know from the stories.
Here you will get not only medals, but also experience points for your profile, which serves both challenges and stories.
Upon reaching the top level, the driver opens up several possibilities, starting with the car and ending up with funds for the profile.
At the same time, an online Autolog feature is connected, which compares your results with those of other players and provides other community features.
One of the most difficult elements to understand is how the last race in history is made.
With the car you get to the subway tunnel (pass), where you start running in the dark on the tracks (pass).
The speedometer marks you between 150 and 200 km/h (pass) and, suddenly, from behind you the convoy of the metro arrives and takes you ahead without further ado.
In the editorial we will surely have a discussion about this for several days, about whether during the programming of the game nobody even thought a little or if the authors really take us for a panda of fools.
The technical part of the game is nothing extraordinary, but at least the overall visual effects are in most cases pleasant, sometimes even superb.
What a shame that, in the most tense moments, the image quality is reduced and, sometimes, in a serious way.
This especially affects accidents where there are many participants involved, when continuous image quality is no longer valid.
The audio is fine and the soundtrack is a matter of taste.
In order to please most of the youth group, the soundtrack belongs to the category "each of their father and mother", but it can be assumed that no one would buy the game just for their music.
The final feel of Need for Speed: The Run is quite confusing.
If the game avoided absolutely silly mistakes, we would have trouble claiming that The Run is the best NFS game of recent years.
It feels like the game isn’t over.
The fun is assured, but be prepared because mistakes will hit your eyes with the strength of airport reflectors.
The choirs of the Carolina University will participate in the concert "Students of Velvet".
The joint celebration of the International Students’ Day and the anniversary of the Velvet Revolution as a musical experience will take place for the third time at the Festa Academica festival.
Twenty choirs from high school and university schools will be presented.
The festival revolves around two concerts on November 17.
“Carolina University has a high participation in the festival.”
Among the current choirs are the choir of the Faculty of Pedagogy and the Faculty of Humanities, on the committee of the festival is the rector Václav Hampl," said the head of the organization, Jakub <0xC4><0x8C>aloun.
