And Thomas’s wife, Ginni, is a prominent conservative activist.
On the other hand, conservatives argue that it is Magistrate Elena Kagan who has an ethical problem, not Scalia and Thomas.
Kagan worked as the attorney general of the Obama administration when the first legal challenges to the law were presented in the court of first instance.
Her critics have pressured Kagan to refrain from seeing the case, saying she was too involved in defending the law to be impartial.
Kagan hasn't given any indication that he's going to.
