During the first year of management of Mario López Valdez, in Sinaloa unemployment and informality have increased, foreign investment has decreased and the economy has contracted.
2011 is a year that will be remembered in the economic history of Sinaloa, it is the first year of the Government of Mario López Valdez, self-described the change, which generated great expectations regarding the advances in the economy, but given the climatic adversity of the beginning of the year, there is no growth, on the other hand there is a deterioration in the main indicators of economic development.
Low temperatures in February, in addition to causing millions of losses to the agricultural sector, limited the chances of the state economy to grow, caused a contraction in overall economic activity of 3.6 percent in the first half of the year, justified mainly by the historic fall of 31.16 percent in agriculture, which affected the dynamism of other economic sectors.
