“What we are seeing is an increase in unemployment that has to do with several factors, including the loss of liquidity in the market due to the effects of a resource restriction by legislation passed in Congress to combat money laundering, and for people who grab dollars illicitly it is not easy for them to work, invest them and use them in something,” he said.
