Interviewed about the possibility of "voting by vote", Mar<0xC3><0xAD>a de los <0xC3><0x81>ngeles Llanderal explained that thanks to the approval of the corresponding guidelines by the General Council of the IEM it will be possible to carry out partial and total counts of the vote by the local electoral body.
In this way, the partial counting of votes, of one or more electoral packages, may take place in the event that: the results of the minutes do not coincide; there is no record of scrutiny and counting in the file of the box or does not work in the possession of the president thereof; or, when there are obvious errors or alterations of the minutes.
In addition, the total count of the vote received in all the boxes of the election may be made when there is evidence that the difference between the candidate presumed to be the winner of the election in question and the candidate who obtained the second place in the vote, is equal to or less than a percentage point; provided that at the beginning of the session there is the express request of the representative of the party and / or coalition that applied for the second.
The total count of the vote may also be made if at the end of the ordinary counting it is established that the difference between the candidate allegedly winning and the one located in second place is equal to or less than a percentage point, provided that there is the express request of the representative of the political party whose candidate was in second place, in which case electoral packages that have been subject to partial counting will be excluded.
It should be mentioned that in this situation is the election of Morelia, where according to the PREP the difference between the first and second place is only 0.16 percent, although without counting the votes of 129 of the 923 total minutes.
