Evicted an occupied farm where macro-partying took place
The invaders had taken over 11 of the 13 floors of the building, in Balmes, France.
The 12 occupants left the farm at noon yesterday without offering resistance
Everything seems to indicate that the nightmare lived by the neighbors of 51 rue de Balmes has come to an end.
Twelve people voluntarily left yesterday at noon the property they occupied illegally, and where they organized macro-parties that despaired of the neighborhood, by court order and without the need for police intervention.
When the operation was finished, the door lock was changed to prevent the situation from recurring.
"From now on there will be an access control," the administrator said.
The squatters, who had invaded 11 of the 13 floors of the building -the rest are inhabited-, took all the electrical installation and part of that of the water, in addition to painting the walls and leaving waste of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
