In addition, the owner of the entertainment venue had had to respond to neighboring complaints for noise, while, she pointed out, the discomfort is not caused by the customers of the discotheque, but by the inhabitants of the house occupied and, above all, the attendees to the parties that were organized there, which had increased their frequency and intensity in recent weeks, according to the angry neighbors of the area.
The manager of the disco explained that the inconvenience was so great that he even reached an agreement with the owner of the property and nine months ago that he "forgives" the rent.
The Urban Guard also confirmed that in recent weeks it had received more complaints from neighbors about the situation.
