Collserola’s classification as a natural park is a result of this idea.
The reference was no longer Central Park but Yellowstone, with wild boars in the role of the Yogi bear.
It was there until, in September, the city council convened a megacompetition consisting of 16 contests for as many access doors to Collserola.
A door refers to the idea of park, without a doubt.
Either that or someone intends to put doors to the field.
The question comes up alone: Collserola, park or mountain?
The contest, both for its purely organizational aspect and for what it implies of reflection on the city, is the topic of conversation among all Barcelona architects.
It is almost a recurring topic to take hold of when two members of this ancient caste of elect recognize each other in an elevator.
