Miguel Roldán, Daniel M<0xC3><0xB2>dol and Marta Bayona: the contest is timely.
For Roldán, after addressing the coastal front "it becomes necessary" to debate about "the mountain front", since the speech of Ildefons Cerd<0xC3><0xA0>, that of the green apples, has not been carried out.
"It is possible to start from the base that the most extensive park in Barcelona is the beach.
Among other things, its great accessibility.
Collserola is more complex, says the architect for whom the title of "doors of Collserola" contains a "lexical trap": we must not think of them "as the accesses to a park, but the delimitation of areas where you have to act".
M<0xC3><0xB2>dol, like Roldán and Bayona with experience in the urban world, calls the proposal an "intellectual challenge" with "some dangers".
Dangers derived from the "uncertainness that it is today to project the public space" after the experience lived in the 80s and that had in the F<0xC3><0xB2>rum area "his song of the swan".
The first fear is the very delimitation of borders over where it can be built.
“Limiting something is fixing the next step,” that is, its overcoming.
"We need to think about new urban planning tools, because the current ones [in reference to the Metropolitan General Plan (MGP)] can give rise to real disasters."
More closely related to the question, M<0xC3><0xB2>dol thinks that, in simplification, the Vallesana slope of Collserola "can be understood as a park, that of Barcelona, not", for a purely topographical matter.
M<0xC3><0xB2>dol recalls that there is already a work done by the Patronat de Collserola that "should not fall into a broken sack", although he appreciates the opportunity that the city council offers its guild to intervene in this project "from the first moment".
And even more, he understands that the proximity of the mountain to the city is the safe conduit that allows architects to enter into the debate, but "doubt" as to whether it is this technical profile that should lead the multidisciplinary teams ("all a right", points out) that have had to be created: "Architectures should be only a tool".
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that gives the title to this piece is complex, because in the bases of the contest lacks a global vision of Collserola: "16 cross-sectional contests have been called -he says - in the mountain-sea sense, but there is no longitudinal reading, which sees and understands the area as a whole."
This causes, at least in your case, that you have chosen to participate in the 16 contests.
Otherwise, a project for one of the doors may collide in program and definition with that of the architect of the door next door.
In his opinion, however, the city council should ensure that the strip immediately above the Ronda de Dalt should provide, in all its extension, an area of equipment that would effect a smooth transition between the city and the green.
