This was the work of the cale<0xC3><0xB1>o who identified the corpse of Alfonso Cano
A lophoscopicist from Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4, a lophoscopicist from the CTI of Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the top FARC chief: "Alfonso Cano", through the comparison of his fingerprints.
Of the seven loboscopes who work in the CTI section, that week it was the turn of "availability" for Eliazar González, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, González worked in municipalities of El Chocó, where he often had to be interned for more than five days in the jungle to reach the site where the corpses that were to be identified were.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after taking the corresponding courses, specialized in lophoscopy, which is the study of frictional skin, that is, of the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano Eliazar was warned to wear minimum clothes for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for the Cauca in a helicopter from Palmyra.
He knew that he had to identify two corpses and that one of them was suspected to be the man who was leading the world’s oldest guerrilla, so he was asked to carry the decactylar card of Guillermo León Sáenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the research team at the site where the corpse was located, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, as it was very different from the one he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a local farmer, without glasses and much thinner.
But the fingerprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those on the card.
His eye did not fail: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, that he was the chief of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a Sij<0xC3><0xAD>n dactyloscopist from Cali, the recognition made by President Juan Manuel Santos to Eliazar González, at the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
A lot of people don't know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin of error, that can become key in the resolution of crimes.
In addition to identifying corpses, loboscopes support investigations into crimes such as theft and homicide and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When captured, many criminals present fake ballots or have no papers.
We take the fingerprint and search them in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, it was up to him to remove a piece of wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to take out a safe full of jewelry and money.
"The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to make a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the fingerprint of the whole hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts," he recalled.
Fingerprints can also rule out or reassert suspects in homicide cases.
They recently found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
The investigation determined that a family member could be suspected of the crime and, indeed, a fingerprint on the bottle matched.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the murderer, it does place him at the crime scene.
A CTI typist explained that on the objects "the fingerprints are taken with chemical or physical reagents."
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the impressions are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
“The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians,” the CTI expert said.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI television show.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes imprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective matching is performed.
