The Committee of Experts also calls for the training of health professionals in the duty to respect the fact that a patient refuses assistance at the end of his life without fear of facing a complaint.
In the area of palliative care, the committee calls for governments, health care institutions and doctors to work together to ensure the best palliative care, not just in cases of cancer.
